    {
      "id": "bd13f2fe818682535b2079af60d6635f37d133ac",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-07 15:22:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nElena - Looking at the el8.1 test results, we do need the oversubscribe flag for mpirun to work. The problem is that, we set MPIRUN_OPTIONS before we call init_test_env() and, thus, the “--oversubscribe” flag is not set in our environment.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9e9f4bfb42b91ed78113c92a8e1ec4d028d05220",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-07 15:22:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nMinh - Could we add the “--oversubscribe” option when we set the MPIRUN_OPTIONS variable or move “--mca boot ssh” to init_test_env() as this patch does for oversubscribe? Or is there a better solution? It seem like we should be consistent; set all mpirun options in one place. \nWe set the MPIRUN_OPTIONS environment variables in autotest in external/mecturk/mecturk-ncli.sh",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d5127037180f7ae60feee5a07abf063c27f9a2c8",
      "author": {
